    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Psidium ramboanum are its antioxidant activity, which can prevent cell damage and oxidative stress. The plant's antimicrobial properties are attributed to the presence of bioactive compounds such as saponins and volatile oils, which inhibit the growth of various microorganisms. Additionally, Psidium ramboanum exhibits anti-inflammatory properties, which may be due to the action of flavonoids and other polyphenolic compounds that reduce inflammation and alleviate pain. Its cardioprotective effects are also noteworthy, as they may be mediated by the bioactive compounds that regulate lipid metabolism and improve cardiovascular health. Furthermore, Psidium ramboanum's antifungal properties are likely due to the presence of compounds that interfere with fungal cell membrane integrity and inhibit fungal growth.",
